HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 109
BY REPRESENTATIVE OWEN
A RESOLUTION
To commend the Rosepine High School Lady Eagles basketball team on winning the
Louisiana High School Athletic Association 2026 Division III Select state
championship.
WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize the Rosepine High School Lady Eagles
for their impressive season and to commend the team on winning the 2026 Division III
Select state championship; and
WHEREAS, the Lady Eagles captured the 2026 Division III Select state title by
defeating Holy Savior Menard, 42-34, in the championship match at the University Center
in Hammond, Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, Rosepine's Case James led the team with fourteen points; Marli Jones
sealed the victory by scoring five points in overtime; and
WHEREAS, the Lady Eagles have three girls basketball state titles over the past four
seasons; and
WHEREAS, the Rosepine High School Lady Eagles coaches and players are most
deserving of the highest recognition for their outstanding achievements.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend the Rosepine High School Lady Eagles
basketball team on winning the Louisiana High School Athletic Association 2026 Division
III Select state championship and does hereby encourage the coaches and players to continue
their excellent work and always strive for greatness in competition.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
